  "//": "Default nbx-guard operator config, installed to ~/.nbx-guard/config.json. This single file is the friendly alternative to exporting NBX_GUARD_* / NETBOX_* env vars — set everything here once. EDIT netbox_url to your NetBox, then choose ONE token source: put the token in your OS keychain and reference it with token_cmd (e.g. macOS 'security find-generic-password -s netbox -w', Linux 'secret-tool lookup service netbox' or 'pass show netbox/token'), OR read it from a file with token_file (Docker/K8s secret, systemd credential), OR keep NETBOX_TOKEN in the environment. NEVER put the raw token in this file — a 'netbox_token' key is refused. The environment always wins over this file, so an env var overrides any value here. Optional connection keys: state_dir, branching, branch, http_timeout_ms. Governance: this default registers every NetBox 4.5 object type so an agent can QUERY the full data model out of the box, and creatable_resources is ['*'] so 'nbxg create' may make NEW objects of any registered type — but every create is still approval-gated (plan -> approve -> apply) and audited. UPDATE governance stays default-deny per field. auto_approve:false keeps the manual approval gate on; set it true only for your own isolated branch/sandbox work (pair with branching) — audit and backups are always kept. The installer never overwrites an existing config; a refreshed default is saved alongside as config.json.default.",

